<p>I'm working on an ASP.NET MVC 5 application. For some reason, certain properties of my model are being set to null on POST to the controller.</p>  <p>E.g.</p>  <p><strong>EDIT</strong></p>  <p>Here is my GET which creates the model:</p>  <pre><code>[HttpGet] public ActionResult AddStuff(long anId) {     myViewModel model;     var otherModels = _myApi.getItems(anId);     model = new myViewModel(id, otherModels);     return View(model); } </code></pre>  <p><strong>END OF EDIT</strong></p>  <p>I have a model that contains an IEnumerable collection other models.</p>  <pre><code>public class myViewModel {     public myViewModel ()     {         // empty ctor required for mvc post     }      public myViewModel (long someId, IEnumerable&lt;myOtherViewModel&gt; otherModels)     {         SomeId = id;         OtherModels = otherModels;     }      public long SomeId { get; set; }     public IEnumerable&lt;myOtherViewModel&gt; OtherModels { get; set; } } </code></pre>  <p>And a view that displays this collection</p>  <pre><code>    @model myViewModel      @{       ViewBag.Title = "A Title";       Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";     }      @using (Html.BeginForm("AddStuff", "MyController", method: FormMethod.Post, routeValues: new {id = @Model.SomeId}, htmlAttributes: new {role = "form"}))     {         @* stuff here *@         &lt;button type="submit" class="btn btn-success"&gt;             &lt;i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;                 Accept         &lt;/button&gt;          @Html.HiddenFor(d =&gt; d.SomeId)     } </code></pre>  <p>Finally my controller:</p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost] public ActionResult AddStuff(long id, myViewModel model) {     //stuff here } </code></pre>  <p>For some reason, my model is passed to the POST method of my controller fine except that the collection property of other models is set to null. The GET request works fine and the view is displaying the model's OtherModels collection correctly. Is there something I'm missing when grabbing the view model in a POST method?</p>  <p>Thanks.</p>